# Soundness and Excess Flow Base Enclosure Test Script
This script is to be used to perform soundness and excess flow checks on the Smart Regulator Base Enclosure

## Prerequisite
1. Install python 3.11
2. Add python to path
3. Install git(latest version)
4. Add git to path

## Installation
__Note__: The following commands are to be run in the _terminal_(Command Prompt/Powershell/terminal) 

1. Open command prompt(or your preferred terminal)   

2. Clone the repository using the command:
```
git clone https://Ndungu_mwangi@bitbucket.org/paygoenergy/fmcd_bottom_assembly_inline.git
```

3. Navigate to the cloned directory

4. Switch to the _base_assembly_sef_ branch:
```
git switch base_assembly_sef
```
5. On the terminal, navigate to the _script_ folder by running the command below:
```
cd fmcd_bottom_assembly_inline\script
```

6. Install the modules required by running the command below:
```
py -m pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## Environment
1. Download and setup [Visual Studio Code](https://code.visualstudio.com/)

## Usage
1. Navigate to the __src__ folder.
2. Open the config.txt file
3. Update the file with the correct configs:
    ```
        type:inline
        s_type:base_enclosure_sef
        db:PROD
        FR1_LPM:17.33
        FR2_LPM:1
        leak_test:manual
        PRESS_THRESH:150
    ```
4. Save the changes and close the file
5. Navigate back to the parent folder(_script_)
6. Run batch script: run_script